This paper is about the analysis of biases in summarization systems and their dependence on the corpus. It involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques and machine learning algorithms, which are commonly used in the fields of computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
